info.description: This API allows shopping and booking with IATA's New Distribution Capabilities (NDC) standard. It provides aggregated shopping capabilities (AirShopping), detailed offer description (OfferPrice), flight seat selection (SeatAvailability) and booking flight reservations (OrderCreate). Some fields in our API (when noticed) use the PADIS Standard v16.1. Find more information here
info.title: AirGateway NDC JSON API

post.description: AirDocIssue the ability to pay for the held booking.

Get a list of offers for provided O&D, dates and travelers. There are three types of AirShopping request:
(one-way) -> For this airshopping, the array of OriginDestination´s must have only one element.
(round-trip) -> For this airshopping, the array of OriginDestination´s must have only two elements, and the arrival of the second element must be the same that the departure of the first element.
(multi-city) -> For this airshopping, the array of OriginDestination´s can have an unlimited quantity of elements.
This method allows async behaviour by sending AG-Connection header with keep-alive value. If a request is received with this header, response will be real-time json streaming so API will return offers as soon as they are received from providers and parsed. Streaming responses are line delimited JSON. You can see an example here.
If AG-Connection is not sent, all responses from providers will be parsed together (it will be slow since it needs to wait for all provider's responses) and there will be only a response with format specified here.
As an additional header option you can control maximum per provider offers in response. Use AG-Per-Provider-Limit header with integer number value.
